{"questionId":"27970","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>At Mirabooka Primary School, a survey found that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>68</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of students have a dog and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>36</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of&nbsp;students have a cat. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of students have both a dog and a cat.</p>\n<p>This information can be represented in the following Venn diagram, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>&nbsp;represent the percentage of students within each region.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/70d061334915aadefa71688aa34b40032252c269.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Find the value of</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>%</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Based on their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>, follow through for parts (i) and (iii), but only if it does not contradict the given information. Follow through for part (iv) but only if the total is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>%</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27970","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.4a.iv","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"q.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.iv","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}